args: (I pushed Mariti so hard I lost my balance\nand now I'm gonna fall in the hole!)
Owww... Wait, huh? How am I in\nthe courtyard?
And was it always decorated\nfor Halloween like this?
We're late! We're late! For a very\nimportant date! And at this rate,\nthe tea party will have to wait!
Uh, why are you wearing your\nHalloween costume, Althemia?
Error detected. Today's decorations\nare for Dragonyule.
Holy what?! The decorations all just\nchanged from Halloween to Dragonyule!
No, no, no! They said they wanted\nHalloween decorations!
(Okay, I have no idea what's\ngoing on right now.)
Althemia? Who is that? I am the Hatter.

Don't up and shout like that! And more
importantly, if you've the time to bumble
about, you've the time to help me prepare
this afternoon's tea party!
Good. You can prepare the tea\nand pancakes.
Are you mad? Today is the unbirthday of\nthe Kingdom of Balberia—and the day of\nthe royal tea party!
Balberia? And wait, what's an unbirthday?

Any day that isn't a royal birthday is an
unbirthday, which makes it a tea party day.
Now then, the recipe is on the desk.
Do take care of it, now. Ta!
I think I've ended up in weirdoland...
Wait, didn't the prince say there were\nlots of other worlds besides our own?\nThis must just be one of those!
Oh geez, but how am I gonna get home?
Still, I guess I should help out first.\nIf I don't, Althemia—er, I mean,\nthe Hatter—will be very cross!

Let's see... Okay, so this is a recipe to
make tea and pancakes for one person,
and there's also a list of everyone coming
to the party.
So how much water do I need here?\nJust gotta multiply... Um... How do you\nmultiply big numbers again...?
Oh, blech! This tea's so weak it tastes\nlike nothing!
Hello, my sweet and charming young lady!\nYou appear to have finished the tea.
I do rather like the ring of that name,\nbut please call me the March Hare.
If I might return the subject, however,\nI must transport your finished tea now.
No, stop! That tea is super weak!
Super weak tea, you say?\nWhy, that's perfect!
You simply must let me convey this most\nsublime beverage to the table at once!
Oh geez. I hope this isn't a bad idea...
Oh, that's right! I gotta make pancakes!
Oh, blech AGAIN. I mixed up the sugar\nand salt, and now the pancakes taste like\nanchovies. I can't serve this—they'll hurl!
Hey, Laxi. No, probably not. ...Uh, wait.\nWho are you, actually?
We are dolls. Twins. I am the elder.
I told you, I am... Oh, never mind.\nHave you made the pancakes?
A salty pancake? You've good taste!

Indeed! After all, people can't be picky.
Sometimes a person must eat sweet,
and sometimes a person must eat salty,
irregardless of what they want!
They ran off with the pancakes...
They all seemed impressed with my work,\nbut I still have a pretty bad feeling...
Hear ye, hear ye! Stand and recognize the\ncoming of the great kings of Balberia!
That there is the younger-brother king\nof Balberia, and next to him is the\nelder-brother king.
The younger is kind, but the elder is hard\nto please and becomes quite cross when\nthings aren't done perfectly.
I thank you for holding my elder brother's\nunbirthday tea party today.
Now, Brother, let us partake of the tea\nthat has been prepared for us.
PFFFFFFFT! Why, this is TERRIBLE!\nIt's just hot water with a couple of sticks\nthrown in for texture!
Now now, Brother! Let's eat some of the\npancakes. They look well-cooked and\ndelicious if I do say so myself.
PFFFFFFFFT! Salty! So salty! It's like\nsandpaper scraping across my tongue!
How DARE you expect me to eat and\ndrink something this disgusting!
Do you think I'm a fool? Is that it?\nShall I cavort and caper about for your\ngrim amusement?!
You will take responsibility for this\nand go DIRECTLY TO JAIL!
SILENCE! This kingdom is under\nMY dominion!
And not just you, but also the Hatter,\nthe March Hare, and the twin dolls!\nTo jail with the whole lot of you!
The weak tea and salty pancakes were\nall my fault. None of the others have\ndone anything wrong.
Ah. Then you will go to jail instead?
Everyone makes mistakes, my brother.\nYou need not be so harsh on them.
Fine. If YOU go to jail in their place,\nI will forgive them their crimes.
No! Please, Mr. Elder-Brother King!\nHave mercy!
And why should I show clemency to the\ngirl who attempted to poison me?
Oh, fine! Just don't start bawling.
I will show mercy...IF you can host a\ntea party that is to my satisfaction!
(I have to save the younger brother,\nbut I have no idea how to host a party\nthat will satisfy the older one!)
